Aetodactylus.label: Aetodactylus
Aetodactylus.description: Aetodactylus is a genus of ornithocheirid pterodactyloid pterosaur. It is known from a lower jaw discovered in Upper Cretaceous rocks of northeastern Texas, United States. Wikipedia

Acristavus.label: Acristavus
Acristavus.description: Acristavus is a genus of saurolophine dinosaur. Fossils have been found from the Campanian Two Medicine Formation in Montana and Wahweap Formation in Utah. The type species A. gagslarsoni was named in 2011. Wikipedia

Agama (genus).label: Agama
Agama (genus).description: An agama is any one of the various small, long-tailed, insect-eating lizards of the genus Agama. The agamid genus is composed of at least 37 species across Africa, where they are the most common lizard. Wikipedia

Amazonsaurus.label: Amazonsaurus
Amazonsaurus.description: Amazonsaurus is a genus of diplodocoid sauropod dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous Period of what is now South America. It would have been a large-bodied quadrupedal herbivore with a long neck and whiplash tail. Wikipedia

Agkistrodon contortrix.label: Agkistrodon contortrix
Agkistrodon contortrix.description: Agkistrodon contortrix is a species of venomous snake endemic to North America, a member of the Crotalinae subfamily. The common name for the species is the copperhead. Wikipedia

African softshell turtle.label: African softshell turtle
African softshell turtle.description: The African softshell turtle or Nile softshell turtle is a large species of turtle from fresh-water and brackish habitats in Africa and the Near East. Wikipedia

Amphisbaenia.label: Amphisbaenia
Amphisbaenia.description: Amphisbaenia is a group of usually legless squamates, comprising over 180 extant species. Amphisbaenians are characterized by long bodies, reduction or loss of the limbs, and rudimentary eyes. Wikipedia

American legless lizard.label: American legless lizard
American legless lizard.description: The family Anniellidae, known as American legless lizards, contains six species in a single genus Anniella A. pulchra, the California legless lizard, the rare, A. geronimensis, Baja California legless lizard, and four more discovered in 2013. Wikipedia

Andesaurus.label: Andesaurus
Andesaurus.description: Andesaurus is a genus of basal titanosaurian sauropod dinosaur which existed during the middle of the Cretaceous Period in South America. Like most sauropods, it would have had a small head on the end of a long neck and an equally long tail. Wikipedia

Angonoka tortoise.label: Angonoka tortoise
Angonoka tortoise.description: The angonoka tortoise is a critically endangered species of tortoise endemic to Madagascar. It is also known as the angonoka, ploughshare tortoise, Madagascar tortoise, or Madagascar angulated tortoise. Wikipedia

Aniliidae.label: Aniliidae
Aniliidae.description: The Aniliidae are a monotypic family created for the monotypic genus Anilius that contains the single species A. scytale. Common names include false coral snake and pipe snake. It is found in South America. Wikipedia

Antarctosaurus.label: Antarctosaurus
Antarctosaurus.description: Antarctosaurus is a genus of titanosaurian sauropod dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous Period of what is now South America. Wikipedia

Angulomastacator.label: Angulomastacator
Angulomastacator.description: Angulomastacator is a genus of duck-billed dinosaur from the Campanian-age Aguja Formation of Big Bend National Park, Texas. It is known from a single specimen, TMM 43681–1, a partial left maxilla. Wikipedia

Argentine tortoise.label: Argentine tortoise
Argentine tortoise.description: The Argentine tortoise is a species of turtle in the family Testudinidae. It is exclusively found in Argentina, in spite of its scientific name referring to Chile. Wikipedia

Argentine snake-necked turtle.label: Argentine snake-necked turtle
Argentine snake-necked turtle.description: The Argentine snake-necked turtle, also known as the South American snake-necked turtle is a species of turtle, known for the long neck which gave it its name. Wikipedia

Araripedactylus.label: Araripedactylus
Araripedactylus.description: Araripedactylus was a large genus of pterodactyloid pterosaur, known from a single wing bone found in the Early Cretaceous-age Santana Formation of Brazil. Wikipedia

Aspidites.label: Aspidites
Aspidites.description: Aspidites is a genus of pythons endemic to Australia. The name can be translated as "shield bearer" and pertains to the symmetrically shaped head scales. Currently, two species are recognized. Wikipedia

Balkan pond turtle.label: Balkan pond turtle
Balkan pond turtle.description: The Balkan pond turtle or western Caspian turtle is a species of turtles in the family Geoemydidae. Wikipedia

Barrosasaurus.label: Barrosasaurus
Barrosasaurus.description: Barrosasaurus is a genus of titanosaurian sauropod dinosaur, first described by paleontologists Leonardo Salgado and Rodolfo Coria in 2009. The fossils, consisting of three fossil dorsal vertebrae, are well-preserved but incomplete. Wikipedia

Baurutitan.label: Baurutitan
Baurutitan.description: Baurutitan was a genus of sauropod dinosaur that appeared in the Late Cretaceous Period. This plant eater grew up to 79 feet long. It was a titanosaur which lived in what is now present-day Brazil. Wikipedia

Beauty rat snake.label: Beauty rat snake
Beauty rat snake.description: The beauty rat snake, also known as the cave racer, is a species of long, slender, semi-arboreal snake that is native to East and Southeast Asia. Several subspecies are recognized. Wikipedia

Bitis arietans.label: Bitis arietans
Bitis arietans.description: Bitis arietans is a venomous viper species found in savannah and grasslands from Morocco and western Arabia throughout Africa except for the Sahara and rain forest regions. Wikipedia

Berberosaurus.label: Berberosaurus
Berberosaurus.description: Berberosaurus is a genus of neotheropod dinosaur, possibly a ceratosaur, from the Pliensbachian-Toarcian-age Lower Jurassic Toundoute Continental Series found in the High Atlas of Toundoute, Ouarzazate, Morocco. Wikipedia

Bog turtle.label: Bog turtle
Bog turtle.description: The bog turtle is a semiaquatic turtle endemic to the eastern United States. It was first scientifically described in 1801 after an 18th-century survey of Pennsylvania. Wikipedia

Bitis peringueyi.label: Bitis peringueyi
Bitis peringueyi.description: Bitis peringueyi is a venomous viper species found in Namibia and southern Angola. No subspecies are currently recognized. Wikipedia

Bitis schneideri.label: Bitis schneideri
Bitis schneideri.description: Bitis schneideri is a venomous viper species found in a small coastal region that straddles the border between Namibia and South Africa. This is the smallest species in the genus Bitis and possibly the world's smallest viperid. Wikipedia

Bolson tortoise.label: Bolson tortoise
Bolson tortoise.description: The Bolson tortoise, also called the Mexican giant tortoise or Yellow-margined tortoise, is a species of tortoise from North America. Of the four North American tortoise species, it is the largest, having a carapace length of about 46 cm. Wikipedia

Bitis gabonica.label: Bitis gabonica
Bitis gabonica.description: Bitis gabonica, commonly known as the Gaboon viper, is a venomous viper species found in the rainforests and savannas of sub-Saharan Africa. Wikipedia

Boiga dendrophila.label: Boiga dendrophila
Boiga dendrophila.description: The gold-ringed cat snake or mangrove snake is a species of rear-fanged colubrid. It is one of the biggest cat snake species, averaging 6–8 feet in length. Wikipedia

Boomslang.label: Boomslang
Boomslang.description: The boomslang is a large, venomous snake in the family Colubridae. Wikipedia

Brachauchenius.label: Brachauchenius
Brachauchenius.description:
Brachauchenius is an extinct genus of pliosaurid that lived in America during the Cretaceous.
The type species, Brachauchenius lucasi, lived in the Western Inland Sea of North America around 93.5-89.3 ... Wikipedia

Brachyophidium.label: Brachyophidium
Brachyophidium.description: Brachyophidium is a monotypic genus created for the nonvenomous shield tail snake species, Brachyophidium rhodogaster, endemic to southern India. No subspecies are currently recognized. Wikipedia

Candoia carinata.label: Candoia carinata
Candoia carinata.description: Candoia carinata, known commonly as the Pacific Ground Boa or the Pacific Keel-scaled Boa, is a species of snake in the Boidae family. It is found in Indonesia, New Guinea, and the Bismarck Archipelago. Wikipedia

Brookesia.label: Brookesia
Brookesia.description: Brookesia is a genus of chameleons found in Madagascar, that range from small to very small in size, and are known collectively as leaf chameleons. Wikipedia

Box turtle.label: Box turtle
Box turtle.description: The box turtle is a genus of turtle native to North America. It is also known as the box tortoise, although box turtles are terrestrial members of the American pond turtle family, and not members of the tortoise family. Wikipedia

Camposaurus.label: Camposaurus
Camposaurus.description: Camposaurus is a coelophysoid dinosaur genus from the Norian stage of the Late Triassic period of North America. The pertinent fossil remains date back to the early to middle Norian stage, and is widely regarded as the oldest known neotheropod. Wikipedia

Camelotia.label: Camelotia
Camelotia.description: Camelotia was a genus of prosauropod or sauropod dinosaur from the Late Triassic of what is now England. Wikipedia

Carinodens.label: Carinodens
Carinodens.description: Carinodens is a genus of mosasaur. It was named in 1969 as a replacement for Compressidens, which was already in use for a mollusk. Measuring approximately 3.5 metres in length, it is one of the smallest known mosasaurs. Wikipedia

Chamaeleo.label: Chamaeleo
Chamaeleo.description: Chamaeleo is a genus of chameleons found primarily in the mainland of sub-saharan Africa, but a few species are also present in northern Africa, southern Europe and southern Asia east to India and Sri Lanka. Wikipedia

Cerasinops.label: Cerasinops
Cerasinops.description: Cerasinops was a small ceratopsian dinosaur. It lived during the Campanian of the late Cretaceous Period. Its fossils have been found in Two Medicine Formation, in Montana. Wikipedia

Chitra (genus).label: Chitra
Chitra (genus).description: Chitra is a genus of turtles of the family Trionychidae. Wikipedia

Causus resimus.label: Causus resimus
Causus resimus.description: Causus resimus is a venomous viper species found in isolated populations distributed across tropical Africa. No subspecies are currently recognized. Wikipedia

Chamaeleo chamaeleon.label: Common chameleon
Chamaeleo chamaeleon.description: The common chameleon or Mediterranean chameleon is the only species of Chamaleonidae native to Europe. Wikipedia

Clidastes.label: Clidastes
Clidastes.description:
Clidastes is an extinct genus of mosasaur lizard from marine environments of the Late Cretaceous.
Clidastes was an agile and fast swimmer that cruised the surface or shallow waters hunting for fish, flying reptiles and anything that got too close. Wikipedia

Chinese water dragon.label: Chinese water dragon
Chinese water dragon.description: Chinese Water Dragon is a monotypic agamid lizard native to East and Southeast Asia. It is also known as Asian Water Dragon, Thai Water Dragon, and Green Water Dragon. Wikipedia

Chuandongocoelurus.label: Chuandongocoelurus
Chuandongocoelurus.description: Chuandongocoelurus named after the Chuandong in Sichuan Province, China, was a genus of tetanuran theropod dinosaur first described by Chinese paleontologist He in 1984. Wikipedia

Conolophus.label: Conolophus
Conolophus.description: The Galápagos land iguanas comprise the genus Conolophus of the Galápagos Islands. The name Conolophus is derived from two Greek words conos meaning "spiny" and lophos meaning "crest" or "plume", ... Wikipedia

Coral snake.label: Coral snake
Coral snake.description: Coral snakes are a large group of elapid snakes that can be subdivided into two distinct groups, Old World coral snakes and New World coral snakes. Wikipedia

Condorraptor.label: Condorraptor
Condorraptor.description: Condorraptor is a genus of megalosauroid theropod dinosaur. It lived during the Middle Jurassic in what is now Argentina, Canadon Asfalto Formation. The type species, described in 2005, is Condorraptor currumili. Wikipedia

Corn snake.label: Corn snake
Corn snake.description: The Red Cornsnake, corn snake, or red rat snake, is a North American species of rat snake that subdues its small prey by constriction. Wikipedia

Crocodylus novaeguinae.label: Crocodylus novaeguineae
Crocodylus novaeguinae.description: The New Guinea crocodile is a small species of crocodile found on the island of New Guinea where there are two geographically isolated populations. Wikipedia

Crotalus atrox.label: Crotalus atrox
Crotalus atrox.description: Crotalus atrox, the western diamondback rattlesnake, is a venomous rattlesnake species found in the United States and Mexico. Wikipedia

Crotalus ruber.label: Crotalus ruber
Crotalus ruber.description: Crotalus ruber is a venomous pit viper species found in southwestern California in the United States and Baja California in Mexico. Three subspecies are currently recognized, including the nominate subspecies described here. Wikipedia

Ctenosaura bakeri.label: Ctenosaura bakeri
Ctenosaura bakeri.description: Ctenosaura bakeri, also known as the Utila iguana, Baker's spinytail iguana, swamper or wishiwilly del suampo, is a critically endangered species of spinytail iguana endemic to the island of Utila, one ... Wikipedia

Cordylidae.label: Cordylidae
Cordylidae.description:
Cordylidae is a family of small to medium sized lizards that occur in southern and eastern Africa. They are commonly known as girdled lizards, spinytail lizards or girdle-tail lizards.
Girdled lizards are diurnal and insectivorous. Wikipedia

Cyclanorbis.label: Cyclanorbis
Cyclanorbis.description: Cyclanorbis is a genus of softshell turtle in the Trionychidae family. Wikipedia

Cycloderma.label: Cycloderma
Cycloderma.description: Cycloderma is a genus of softshell turtle in the Trionychidae family. Wikipedia

Desert tortoise.label: Desert tortoise
Desert tortoise.description: The desert tortoises are species of tortoise native to the Mojave desert and Sonoran desert of the southwestern United States and northwestern Mexico and the Sinaloan thornscrub of northwestern Mexico. Wikipedia

Dakosaurus.label: Dakosaurus
Dakosaurus.description: Dakosaurus is an extinct genus within the family Metriorhynchidae that lived during the Late Jurassic and Early Cretaceous. It was large, with teeth that were serrated and compressed lateromedially. Wikipedia

Diamondback terrapin.label: Diamondback terrapin
Diamondback terrapin.description: The diamondback terrapin or simply terrapin, is a species of turtle native to the brackish coastal swamps of the eastern and southern United States. It belongs to the monotypic genus, Malaclemys. Wikipedia

Dasypeltis.label: Dasypeltis
Dasypeltis.description: Dasypeltis is a genus of colubrid snakes. It is one of only two taxonomic groups of snakes known to have adapted to feed exclusively on eggs. Wikipedia

Ctenosaura.label: Ctenosaura
Ctenosaura.description: Ctenosaura is a lizard genus commonly known as spinytail iguanas or Ctenosaurs. The genus is part of the large lizard family, Iguanidae and is native to Mexico and Central America. Wikipedia

Dibamidae.label: Dibamidae
Dibamidae.description: Dibamidae is a family of legless lizards found in tropical forests. Relatively little is known about the dibamid lizards, which are native to Mexico, Southeast Asia, Indonesia, the Philippine Islands, and western New Guinea. Wikipedia

Diabloceratops.label: Diabloceratops
Diabloceratops.description: Diabloceratops [dee-ab-lo-ser-a-tops] is an extinct genus of centrosaurine ceratopsian dinosaur that lived approximately 79 million years ago during the latter part of the Cretaceous Period in what is now Utah, in the United States. Wikipedia

Dice snake.label: Dice snake
Dice snake.description: The dice snake is a European nonvenomous snake belonging to the family Colubridae, subfamily Natricinae. Wikipedia

Draco volans.label: Draco volans
Draco volans.description:
Draco volans, commonly known as the flying dragon, is a species of lizard endemic to Southeast Asia.
It is a member of the genus of gliding lizards Draco. Wikipedia

Dinilysia.label: Dinilysia
Dinilysia.description: Dinilysia is an extinct genus of snake from the Late Cretaceous of South America. The snake reached a length of 6-10 feet and preyed on smaller animals. Wikipedia

Dracopelta.label: Dracopelta
Dracopelta.description: Dracopelta was an ankylosaurian dinosaur from Portugal, described by Peter Galton in 1980. When Galton described the only known specimen, he referred it to the Kimmeridgian age of the locality of Ribamar. Wikipedia

Euskelosaurus.label: Euskelosaurus
Euskelosaurus.description: Euskelosaurus was a semi-bipedal dinosaur from the Late Triassic. It was a prosauropod that lived in the Late Triassic Period, in present-day South Africa, Lesotho, and Zimbabwe. Wikipedia

False map turtle.label: False map turtle
False map turtle.description: The false map turtle is a species of turtle endemic to the United States. It is a common pet species. Two subspecies are recognized, including the nominotypical subspecies described here. Wikipedia

Flatback sea turtle.label: Flatback sea turtle
Flatback sea turtle.description: The flatback sea turtle is a sea turtle endemic to the continental shelf of Australia. Flatback turtles belong to the sea turtle superfamily Cheloniidae and are the only species found in the genus Natator. Wikipedia

Drusilasaura.label: Drusilasaura
Drusilasaura.description: Drusilasaura is an extinct genus of possible lognkosaurian titanosaur sauropod dinosaur which lived during the late Cretaceous of Santa Cruz Province of southern Patagonia, Argentina. Wikipedia

Ferganasaurus.label: Ferganasaurus
Ferganasaurus.description: Ferganasaurus was a genus of dinosaur first formally described in 2003 by Alifanov and Averianov. The type species is Ferganasaurus verzilini. It was a sauropod similar to Rhoetosaurus. Wikipedia

Forest hinge-back tortoise.label: Forest hinge-back tortoise
Forest hinge-back tortoise.description: The Forest Hinge-back Tortoise, serrated hinge-back tortoise, or Schweigger's tortoise is a species of turtle in the Testudinidae family. Another species, Psammobates oculifer, also goes by the same name of Serrated tortoise. Wikipedia

Eileanchelys.label: Eileanchelys
Eileanchelys.description: Eileanchelys is an extinct genus of primitive turtle from the Middle Jurassic period some 164 million years ago of Britain. Only one species is recorded, Eileanchelys waldmani. Wikipedia

Florida box turtle.label: Florida box turtle
Florida box turtle.description: The Florida box turtle is a subspecies of turtle belonging to the family Emydidae. Wikipedia

Forsten's tortoise.label: Forsten's tortoise
Forsten's tortoise.description: Forsten's tortoise is an endangered species of tortoise found on Sulawesi, Indonesia. I. travancorica is found in the Western Ghats of India and has been considered as a synonym of I. forstenii previously but is now treated as a separate species. Wikipedia

Genyodectes.label: Genyodectes
Genyodectes.description: Genyodectes is a genus of ceratosaurian theropod dinosaur from the Lower Cretaceous of South America. Wikipedia

Gallardosaurus.label: Gallardosaurus
Gallardosaurus.description: Gallardosaurus is a genus of pliosaurid plesiosaur from the Caribbean seaway. It contains the single species Gallardosaurus iturraldei. Gallardosaurus was found in middle-late Oxfordian-age rocks of the Jagua Formation of western Cuba. Wikipedia

Geochelone.label: Geochelone
Geochelone.description:
Geochelone is a genus of tortoises.
Geochelone tortoises, which are also known as typical tortoises or terrestrial turtles, can be found in Africa and Asia. They primarily eat plants. Wikipedia

Geoemydidae.label: Geoemydidae
Geoemydidae.description: The Geoemydidae are the largest and most diverse family in the order Testudines, with about 70 species. The family includes the Eurasian pond and river turtles and Neotropical wood turtles. Wikipedia

Gigantophis.label: Gigantophis
Gigantophis.description: Gigantophis garstini was a giant prehistoric snake which may have measured more than 10 metres, larger than any living species of snake. Before Titanoboa was discovered in Colombia in 2002, it was regarded as the largest snake in history. Wikipedia

Geometric tortoise.label: Geometric tortoise
Geometric tortoise.description: The geometric tortoise is an endangered species of tortoise and one of three members of the genus, Psammobates. It is found in a very small section in the South-Western Cape of South Africa. Wikipedia

Gekkoninae.label: Gekkoninae
Gekkoninae.description: Gekkoninae is a diverse subfamily of Gekkonidae, geckos. It has the most species and genera— over 850 species in 75 genera. Hemidactylus, Cyrtodactylus and Sphaerodactylus alone account for 280 species. Wikipedia

Gobititan.label: Gobititan
Gobititan.description: Gobititan is a genus of dinosaur from the Barremian faunal stage of the Early Cretaceous, approximately 129-125 million years ago. Wikipedia

Geosaurus.label: Geosaurus
Geosaurus.description: Geosaurus is an extinct genus of marine crocodyliform within the family Metriorhynchidae that lived during the Late Jurassic to the Early Cretaceous. Geosaurus was a carnivore that spent much, if not all, its life out at sea. Wikipedia

Glyptemys.label: Glyptemys
Glyptemys.description: Glyptemys is a genus of turtles in the family Emydidae. It comprises two species, the bog turtle and wood turtle, both of which are endemic to North America. Wikipedia

Gold tegu.label: Gold tegu
Gold tegu.description: The gold tegu, also known as golden tegu, common tegu, black tegu and Colombian tegu, is a species of tegu. Its old scientific name was Tupinambis nigropunctatus but it has since renamed to Tupinambis teguixin. Wikipedia

Gongxianosaurus.label: Gongxianosaurus
Gongxianosaurus.description: Gongxianosaurus is a genus of basal sauropod dinosaur from the early Jurassic Period. The only species is Gongxianosaurus shibeiensis. Wikipedia

Gopher tortoise.label: Gopher tortoise
Gopher tortoise.description: The gopher tortoise is a species of the Gopherus genus native to the southeastern United States. The gopher tortoise is seen as a keystone species because it digs burrows that provide shelter for 360 other animal species. Wikipedia

Greater short-horned lizard.label: Greater short-horned lizard
Greater short-horned lizard.description: The short-horned lizard is a small lizard that occurs in North America. Like other horned lizards, it is often wrongly called the "Horned Toad" or "Horny Toad," but it is not a toad at all. It is a reptile, not an amphibian. Wikipedia

Gorgonops.label: Gorgonops
Gorgonops.description: Gorgonops is an extinct genus of therapsid which lived about 260-254 million years ago, during the Late Permian. Wikipedia

Henophidia.label: Henophidia
Henophidia.description: Henophidia is a superfamily of the suborder Serpentes that contains boas, pythons and other snakes. Snakes belonging to superfamily Henophidia are considered to be more primitive than those belonging ... Wikipedia

Graptemys.label: Graptemys
Graptemys.description: Graptemys is a genus of aquatic, freshwater turtles known commonly as map turtles or sometimes sawback turtles, endemic to North America. Wikipedia

Homopholis fasciata.label: Homopholis fasciata
Homopholis fasciata.description: Homopholis fasciata is a small gecko that lives in East Africa. Wikipedia

Gryposaurus.label: Gryposaurus
Gryposaurus.description: Gryposaurus was a genus of duckbilled dinosaur that lived about 83 to 75.5 million years ago, in the Late Cretaceous of North America. Wikipedia

Home's hinge-back tortoise.label: Home's hinge-back tortoise
Home's hinge-back tortoise.description: The Home's hinge-back tortoise is a species of turtle in the Testudinidae family. It is found in Benin, Cameroon, Democratic Republic of the Congo, Ivory Coast, Equatorial Guinea, Gabon, Ghana, Liberia, Nigeria, and possibly Togo. Wikipedia
